			<div id="mdcolumn">
<h1>Why study Computer Science at York?</h1>
<p>There has never been a more exciting time to study Computer Science - it is a subject that involves you in the very make up of the world as technology becomes more and more a part of our lives. But why should you choose to study Computer Science at York? Here's a few reasons why we think you should:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Excellent facilities</strong> - our home on Campus East has been purpose-built for Computer Science. It includes a social learning area and up-to-date lab facilities that are accessible 24 hours a day, seven days a week.</li>
<li>You will have <strong>excellent career prospects</strong> - our graduates are highly sought after in the workplace.</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our <strong>strong links with industry</strong> ensure </span>our courses are up to date in such a dynamic and fast-moving industry. Industry also provides us with excellent placements, to help you put into practice what you have learnt in your degree.</li>
<li>You will be <strong>taught by academics at the cutting edge of their field</strong> - so you are up to date with the latest in Computer Science. The majority of our research is classed as world-leading or internationally excellent.</li>
<li>You can <strong>choose what to study</strong> as you progress through the courses - this can include getting involved in the latest research in the Department.</li>
<li>We are proud of our <strong>high staff-student ratio</strong> - so you can enjoy quality time with academic staff and easy access to your supervisor.</li>
<li>We<strong> teach you Computer Science in a broad and principled way, and the theory as well as the practice</strong>. Our courses give you the thorough grounding in Computer Science that will allow you to pick up languages and techniques easily in the workplace.</li>
<li>We <strong>teach you in a range of ways</strong>, including tutorials, lectures, practical sessions and individual projects.</li>
<li>We provide a <strong>supportive and friendly environment</strong>, including a personal supervisor, to help you get the most out of your time at York.</li>
<li>York has <strong>excellent transportation links</strong> - meaning you can reach London is under two hours, as well as finding the rest of the UK easily accessible.</li>
</ul>
<p><a title="Student life at York" href="http://www.york.ac.uk/study/student-life/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Find out more about why York, the University and city, is a great place to live and study.</a></p>
			
		  </div> 
